{#
  Argument Template
  =================
  Thesis argument structure: Claims, Grounds, Proofs.
  For building and defending scholarly arguments.

  Required Variables:
  - title: Paper title
  - author: Author name(s)
  - abstract: Paper abstract

  Optional Variables:
  - claims: Central claims content
  - grounds: Evidence and justification content
  - proofs: Logical validation content
  - date: Publication date (defaults to \today)
  - bibliography: Bibliography file name (defaults to 'references')

  Usage:
    const context = {
      title: "The Case for Semantic CLIs",
      author: "Academic Author",
      abstract: "This paper argues that...",
      claims: "We claim that RDF integration...",
      grounds: "Evidence from industry adoption...",
      proofs: "Logical demonstration shows..."
    };
#}
